{"word":"H3908 - לַחַשׁ - lachash - lakh'-ash - Charmed","slug":"H3908","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">לַחַשׁ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>lachash"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>lakh'-ash"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Charmed"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DC;&#x05D7;&#x05E9;&#x05C1; - lachash</b> - <i>lakh'-ash</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H3907\">H3907</a>; properly a <i>whisper</i>, that is, by implication (in a good sense) a private <i>prayer</i>, (in a bad one) an <i>incantation</i>; concretely an <i>amulet: - </i>charmed, earring, enchantment, orator, prayer."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3873\">H3873</a>, <a href=\"#/H3907\">H3907</a>, <a href=\"#/H3910\">H3910</a>"}]}